<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2438: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-25T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            25, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.16 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3113. Matter has been repeatedly but informally presented in sense of
                                your 5992 September 23rd, 7 p.m., and therefore renewed pressure for
                                reply for reasons advanced in my 3090 September 22nd, 8 p.m., would
                                appear injudicious at this moment. Foreign Office promise to advise
                                me immediately Japanese reply is received.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>